oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Black Jack Wayne Show - 1958-10-18 - KTVU
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: First recording contains excerpts from the Black Jack Wayne Show from October 18, 1958. Featuring Black Jack Wayne (host) and Johnny Cash (performer) on television station KTVU-TV (Oakland, Calif.) Second recording contains an excerpt from the Ozark Jubilee, featuring Cecil Brower (performer). Third recording contains excerpts from the Black Jack Wayne Show, featuring Black Jack Wayne (host) and the Maddox Brothers And Rose (performers) on television station KTVU-TV (Oakland, Calif.)
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Johnny Cash; Cecil Brower; Maddox Brothers And Rose; Fred Maddox; Rose Maddox; Don Maddox
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Test tones -- Black Jack Wayne introduces Johnny Cash -- Big River (Johnny Cash) -- Black Jack Wayne talks about upcoming shows -- What Do I Care (Johnny Cash) -- Black Jack Wayne talks about Cash's new record -- Folsom Prison Blues (Johnny Cash) -- Cash talks and introduces the next song -- All Over Again (Johnny Cash) -- Black Jack Wayne talks (incomplete) -- [Unidentified fiddle tune] (Cecil Brower fiddle) -- Black Jack Wayne introduces the Maddox Brothers And Rose -- Big Balls In Cow Town (Maddox Brothers And Rose) -- Fa So La (Maddox Brothers And Rose) -- Fred Maddox talks -- Squaws Along The Yukon (Maddox Brothers And Rose) -- Rockin' And Rollin' (Maddox Brothers And Rose) -- Fred Maddox talks about an upcoming show -- The Death Of Rock And Roll (Maddox Brothers And Rose) (incomplete)
